[PATCH v3 3/3] mm: rmap: optimize batched operations for contiguous PTEs

This patch optimizes the batched operations for contiguous PTEs on
architectures that support them (e.g., ARM64).

By leveraging contiguous PTEs, we can further reduce the number of
TLB flushes and improve cache utilization.

This is patch 3 of 3 in the batched rmap series.

